  "prompt": "Will I be arrested reentering the US with a bench warrant?",
  "response": "While I can't provide legal advice, I can offer some general information. Having a bench warrant typically means that a judge has ordered your arrest due to your failure to appear in court or comply with some court order. If you reenter the U.S. with a bench warrant, you could be at risk of arrest, especially if the warrant is discovered during routine procedures, such as a customs check.\n\nAuthorities at the border and at immigration checkpoints have access to various databases, and a bench warrant may show up during their checks. It's important to address any legal issues before traveling to avoid complications. Consulting with an attorney who specializes in this area can provide you guidance tailored to your specific situation.",
